title: Grateful Dead Live at Rosemont Horizon on 1994-03-17
description:
Set 1

Touch Of Gray , Wang Dang Doodle, Althea, Me & My Uncle-> Mexicali Blues, Lazy River Road, Eternity

Set 2

Box Of Rain, Iko Iko, Playin' In The Band-> Uncle John's Band-> Jam-> Drums-> Space-> The Wheel-> All Along The Watchtower-> Morning Dew, E: Rain

reviews.review_text: Morning Dew  This is decent show, this run has tons more energy than the Phoenix shows that I saw the eek before. I was desperate for tickets when I got to Chicago. Romesmont has never been an easy ticket for me. I managed to get one for 15 above cost, people were yelling at me, telling me it was a fake and that they were planning a gate crash. I could hear Touch of Grey, then the guard told me that I had to go to the other side fo the  building, on the outside, the same angry ticketless mob was outside "I told you that it was a fake!". I mentioned that I was on the wrong entry side, by the time I got to the seat. Wang Dang Doodle was finishing, it was pretty unpopulated  where I was, but I had the side stage speakers in front of me, and a prefect view of just about all the band from my seat. I enjoyed Althea,and the dbl Bobby cowboy Uncle-Mexicalli. Lazy River Road had become a favorite first set Jerry song at that point in time,Eternity was standard, I done hate this song, I much preferred it some of the other "new" songs. Box of Rain sounded good, Phil did well. Iko was always fun for me, PITB was good. Drums and Space were not  anything spectacular that I remember, I was happy for the Wheel>watchtower. I was hoping for A Morning Dew going, but wasn't holding  any breath, then it happened. The whole place roared, I felt like we had all been waiting for this song(and its a personal favorite). I know that it was not a flawless Dew, but Jerrys guitar was so clear, it kind sparkled and his voice sounded great. The band seemed to all come together as the song built. If you listen to audience tape, everyone was excited as the song peaked, and what I thought was a good show became  better. The Rain encore was a nice finish.  I then had to go find my one friend that also go in and we were both so excited for the Morning Dew that we couldn't stop laughing and talking about it.
